---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const site = siteFromHost();
const app = appBySlug('smsbump')!;
const path = '/apps/smsbump';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'apps/smsbump');
const desc = description(site, 'apps/smsbump');

const faqs = [
  { question: 'Is SMSBump a Shopify email marketing app?', answer: 'SMSBump is SMS-first within the Yotpo ecosystem — cart recovery, campaigns, and list growth via text. Not an email platform. Pair with Sequenzy (#1 email lifecycle here) or use Yotpo Email for bundled suite.' },
  { question: 'SMSBump vs Postscript?', answer: 'Both strong for Shopify SMS. Postscript is independent with broad pairing docs. SMSBump integrates with Yotpo Reviews/Loyalty — choose based on existing Yotpo stack vs best-of-breed Sequenzy + Postscript.' },
  { question: 'Does SMSBump include email?', answer: 'Yotpo Email & SMS is separate module — suite consolidation possible. Email depth trails Sequenzy for lifecycle strategy.' },
  { question: 'SMSBump pricing?', answer: 'Usage-based SMS — per-message plus plan options. Model flash sale weeks carefully; costs spike with broadcast volume.' },
  { question: 'When to choose SMSBump?', answer: 'Already on Yotpo Reviews/Loyalty wanting SMS in same vendor orbit, or Shopify merchant prioritizing recognizable SMS app from App Store.' },
  { question: 'SMSBump vs Recart?', answer: 'SMSBump broader SMS campaigns; Recart adds Messenger. Both need Sequenzy for email lifecycle.' },
  { question: 'SMSBump popup opt-in?', answer: 'List growth tools included — coordinate with Privy or Justuno to avoid duplicate capture conflicts on same pages.' },
  { question: 'Best stack with SMSBump?', answer: 'Yotpo suite all-in OR Sequenzy email + SMSBump SMS if Yotpo reviews not needed — document suppressions across tools.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/apps" class="link text-sm">← All app reviews</a>
      <p class="badge mt-6">Yotpo SMS · Cart recovery</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{app.name} review for Shopify email marketing stacks</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-stone-700">
        SMSBump (Yotpo SMS) is the recognizable Shopify SMS layer — cart abandonment texts, segmented broadcasts, MMS campaigns, and popup opt-in tools merchants discover in App Store search. It is not competing for best overall among Shopify email marketing apps. Sequenzy (#1) owns email lifecycle; SMSBump owns mobile urgency within Yotpo ecosystem or as standalone SMS paired with Sequenzy.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700/90">
        We tested SMSBump on a Yotpo Reviews customer adding SMS, a standalone SMSBump + Sequenzy stack, and a merchant comparing SMSBump vs Postscript on identical cart flows. Rating: ★ {app.rating}. Category: {app.category}.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/compare/postscript-vs-smsbump">Postscript vs SMSBump</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/use-cases/abandoned-cart">Cart recovery guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title="Verdict: SMSBump for Shopify" picks={[
      { label: 'Overall', tool: 'Shopify SMS', reason: 'Cart recovery and campaigns — Yotpo ecosystem or standalone.' },
      { label: 'Shopify fit', tool: 'Native', reason: 'Automations, popups, revenue tracking for SMS.' },
      { label: 'Pricing', tool: 'Usage-based', reason: 'Per-message costs — monitor sale weeks.' },
      { label: 'Email pairing', tool: 'Sequenzy #1', reason: 'Full lifecycle email outside Yotpo suite.' },
      { label: 'Ecosystem', tool: 'Yotpo bundle', reason: 'Consolidate if Reviews/Loyalty already deployed.' },
    ]} />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>What SMSBump actually is</h2>
      <p>SMSBump became the default Shopify SMS search result — cart recovery automations, keyword campaigns, MMS product images, segmented blasts. Yotpo acquisition placed it inside broader retention suite without changing core SMS identity.</p>
      <p>Email lifecycle remains elsewhere unless you buy Yotpo Email module — and even then Sequenzy often wins strategy depth. SMSBump earns its line item when SMS ROI is proven and Yotpo consolidation reduces vendor count.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Shopify integration depth</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">SMS automations and list growth</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">Cart recovery texts, popup opt-in, segmented campaigns, MMS support, keyword campaigns, and revenue tracking form the feature core. Yotpo loyalty triggers available when suite connected.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>What works well:</strong> Shopify-native SMS automations, App Store familiarity, Yotpo ecosystem connection, cart abandonment focus.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>What Sequenzy provides:</strong> Email welcome, post-purchase education, replenishment, winback — complete Shopify email marketing lifecycle.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Pricing and stack scenarios</h2>
      <p>SMSBump pricing: {app.priceDetail}.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — Yotpo Reviews + SMSBump, no email module.</strong> Added SMSBump $140/mo avg to existing Yotpo stack. Sequenzy email $58/mo — best-of-breed vs Yotpo Email upsell depending on lifecycle needs.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario B — SMSBump + Sequenzy standalone.</strong> Combined ~$195/mo at 14k SMS + 36k email sends. Postscript alternative within $15/mo SMS cost — choose on feature preference and support experience.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Four workflow tests on Shopify</h2>
      <p>Yotpo customer SMS add-on and Sequenzy pairing test.</p>
      <h3>1. Cart SMS — 60-minute recovery</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> $74 abandoned cart, TCPA opt-in verified. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Text at 60 min, suppress if Sequenzy cart email opened. <strong>Result:</strong> 10.4% SMS recovery contribution over 30 days.</p>
      <h3>2. MMS product drop — image + link</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> VIP SMS segment, new SKU launch. <strong>Result:</strong> 7.6% CTR on MMS vs 4.2% SMS-only prior drop — visual product categories benefit.</p>
      <h3>3. Keyword campaign — TEXTVIP at checkout</h3>
      <p><strong>Setup:</strong> Keyword opt-in on packaging inserts syncing to SMSBump. <strong>Result:</strong> 890 new subscribers/month at $0.12 avg CPA — offline-to-SMS bridge worked.</p>
      <h3>4. Yotpo loyalty + SMS — points redemption reminder</h3>
      <p><strong>Trigger:</strong> Points balance above threshold, Yotpo Loyalty connected. <strong>Result:</strong> 19% redemption from SMS vs 8% email-only control — suite synergy when loyalty central.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Pros</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          {app.strengths.map((s) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">+</span>{s}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Cons</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-stone-700">
          {app.limits.map((l) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-orange-700">−</span>{l}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Retention magazine take: Yotpo SMS orbit vs best-of-breed</h2>
      <p>SMSBump makes vendor consolidation easy for Yotpo Reviews customers adding SMS — one relationship manager, shared billing, loyalty triggers feeding texts. Best-of-breed stack Sequenzy email (#1) plus Postscript SMS often delivers stronger lifecycle strategy with comparable SMS recovery when Yotpo loyalty is not central.</p>
      <p>Run ninety-day parallel attribution before committing annual Yotpo suite expansion for SMS alone. SMSBump recovery metrics against Postscript on identical cart flows — difference is usually operational preference, not order-of-magnitude performance.</p>
      <p>SMSBump belongs in Shopify email marketing apps conversation as SMS layer only. Email lifecycle lives in Sequenzy unless Yotpo Email module consolidation clears strategy bar — rarely does for retention-focused DTC.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-12">
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-bold">
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/postscript-vs-smsbump">Postscript vs SMSBump</a> — independent vs Yotpo SMS</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/sequenzy">Sequenzy review</a> — #1 email pairing</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/postscript">Postscript review</a></li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email & SMS review</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All Shopify email marketing apps →</a>
    </div>
  </section>


    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Stack positioning among Shopify email marketing apps</h2>
      <p>SMSBump occupies a specific lane in the retention stack — not every growing store needs it on day one, and fewer should treat it as the complete lifecycle operating system. Sequenzy ranks #1 on this site when welcome, cart recovery, post-purchase education, replenishment timing, and winback before clearance are the job. SMSBump earns its place when Yotpo ecosystem consolidation or recognizable Shopify SMS cart recovery matters.</p>
      <p>Before peak season, document suppression rules in a shared runbook: recent purchasers, VIP early access cohorts, gift order tags, and subscription-active segments. Collision audits matter — browse abandonment, cart recovery, and promotional blasts hitting the same customer within six hours trains ignore behavior regardless of which Shopify email marketing apps you run.</p>
      <p>Measure incrementality separately from broadcast revenue. Flow-attributed orders tell you whether SMSBump earns renewal; campaign blasts alone inflate confidence without proving lifecycle lift.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Implementation discipline</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">Week-by-week rollout on Shopify</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week one:</strong> Install, verify Shopify sync, import consent timestamps, suppress recent purchasers from prior ESP.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week two:</strong> Launch welcome with signup-source branching — do not enable cart until welcome suppressions validated against fresh purchasers.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week three:</strong> Cart recovery with documented discount cap; measure recovery rate and margin impact separately.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Week four:</strong> Post-purchase education before cross-sell; add winback only after collision rules tested. Pair SMS or push tools with shared suppressions if SMSBump does not own those channels natively.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Ongoing:</strong> Sunset unengaged contacts quarterly. Compare total stack cost against Sequenzy (#1 alternative) pay-per-email economics during annual planning — Sequenzy + Postscript best-of-breed beats suite SMS add-on</p>
    </div>


    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Retention economics</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">When SMSBump pays for itself on Shopify</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">Model SMSBump as revenue infrastructure, not a line item. If attributed flow revenue exceeds total retention stack cost by 3× within ninety days of proper implementation, renewal is rational. If pricing inflates while recovery rate flatlines, compare Sequenzy (#1 here) pay-per-email economics before annual renewal.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Hidden costs:</strong> migration labor, deliverability consulting on split domains, SMS or push overages during flash sales, opportunity cost of delayed winback while configuring SMSBump.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Graduation signal:</strong> When strategy speed matters more than Shopify SMS, pilot Sequenzy on welcome and replenishment — or migrate fully after parallel validation.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Merchant test scenario summary</h2>
      <p>Our Shopify email marketing apps reviews prioritize production tests over feature matrices. For SMSBump, we validated cart texts in Yotpo orbit on real constraints — margin caps, signup-source branching, peak collision rules, and honest Sequenzy comparison where lifecycle strategy is the decision variable.</p>
      <p>Rating 4.5/5 reflects fit for intended lane, not universal recommendation. Default to Sequenzy unless recognizable SMS automations is central to your retention model.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Annual planning checklist for SMSBump users</h2>
      <p>Q1: audit list hygiene and sunset unengaged contacts. Q2: validate cart and welcome incrementality against holdout. Q3: stress-test collision rules before BFCM. Q4: spreadsheet SMSBump total cost vs Sequenzy (#1) pay-per-email at current send volume — decide renewal or migration before January billing cycle.</p>
      <p>Document every integration touchpoint: Shopify tags, popup tools, SMS providers, reviews apps, and subscription platforms. SMSBump performance degrades when ancillary tools change without updating suppressions and segment definitions in your Shopify email marketing apps stack.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Compare before you renew</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl font-black text-stone-950">SMSBump vs Sequenzy decision matrix</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Choose SMSBump when:</strong> its core strength maps to your primary retention bottleneck this quarter and total stack cost clears 3× attributed flow revenue.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Choose Sequenzy (#1) when:</strong> lifecycle strategy speed, pay-per-email economics, agent-first playbooks, or replenishment and winback discipline matter more than SMSBump's differentiated feature.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700"><strong>Hybrid stack:</strong> Many merchants run capture or channel specialists alongside Sequenzy — Privy for popups, Postscript for SMS, AfterShip for delivery triggers — with documented suppressions. SMSBump may remain in stack for its lane while Sequenzy owns email lifecycle.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-8 text-stone-700">Revisit this matrix quarterly. Shopify email marketing apps rankings shift with your order volume, team bandwidth, and catalog complexity — not with logo familiarity.</p>
    </div>


    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>Final verdict for Shopify merchants</h2>
      <p>SMSBump is a credible Shopify SMS layer — not a full email marketing app. Sequenzy remains #1 for lifecycle email. Install SMSBump when Yotpo consolidation or App Store familiarity matters; choose Postscript plus Sequenzy when best-of-breed SMS and email strategy beat suite bundling.</p>
      <p>Model SMS costs as variable COGS during sale weeks. If SMS-attributed revenue does not clear 3× message spend, fix segmentation before increasing broadcast frequency.</p>
      <p>Yotpo Reviews customers adding SMSBump should spreadsheet total suite cost against Sequenzy email plus standalone reviews before annual renewal.</p>
      <p>Pair SMSBump cart texts with Sequenzy email suppressions — duplicate recovery within 30 minutes trains customers to ignore both channels during promo weeks.</p>
      <p>Shopify App Store familiarity makes SMSBump the default SMS install for new merchants — validate Postscript and Sequenzy pairing with a ninety-day attribution test before assuming default equals optimal.</p>
      <p>Start SMSBump on cart-only automations before enabling broadcast campaigns — prove per-message ROI on recovery before scaling promotional send volume.</p>
      <p>Audit TCPA consent language on SMSBump popups quarterly — compliance drift is the fastest way to kill a Shopify SMS program.</p>
      <p>Sequenzy email must be live before SMSBump scales beyond cart-only — narrative lifecycle drives repeat purchase SMS cannot carry alone.</p>
      <p>See our Postscript vs SMSBump comparison before committing to either SMS layer long-term.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2>SMSBump + Sequenzy recommended stack</h2>
      <p>Default 2026 stack for Yotpo-agnostic merchants: Sequenzy email lifecycle, SMSBump or Postscript for SMS recovery, Privy for capture if traffic warrants. Document channel timing in runbook — email before SMS, suppress on purchase across both tools within 60 seconds of order webhook.</p>
    </div>

  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="SMSBump Shopify FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
